8.List

ordered list <ol> 
inordered list <ul>

<ol type="i">
 <li><a href="url">Apple</li> <!--<list iterm> -->
 <li>Oranges
   <ol>
     <li>item1</li>
   </ol>
 </li>
 <li>banana</li>
</ol>

9.

description list -dl
description term - dt
describe the description term - dd
<dl>
 <dt>Apple</dt>
 <dd>- They are red</d>
</dl>

10.
table row (horizontal row) --->tr
table data -td
coloum title -th
colspan = "2" means particular data occupy 2 coloum in table

<table>
 <thead>
  <caption>List of Numbers</caption>
  <tr>
   <th>num1</th>
   <th>num2</th>
   <th>num3</th>
  </tr>
 </thead>
 <tbody>
  <tr>
   <td colspan="2"> one </td>
   <td> two </td>
  </tr>
 </tbody>
</table>

11.
2 basic ways to display elements
block elements 
inline elements

inline elements
eg tags:
1 <a href="#">link1</a>
  <a href="#">links2</a>
2 <span>span1</span>
  <span>span2</span>

block elements
eg:
1 <p>Paragraph1</p>
  <p>Paragraph2</p>
2 <div>div1</div>
  <div>div2</div>


12.Inputs and Forms

  <input type="text" value="Enter your username" />
  <input type="password" />
  <input type="date" />
  <input type="file" />
  <input type="range"/>
  <input name="btn" type="radio"/>
  <input type="submit"/>

  <textarea rows="10" cols="30">
    Enter a paragraph
  </textarea> 

  <form>
    <input type="submit"/>
  </form>

13.
iframe used to display other website inside our webpage

<iframe src="URL" frameboarder="0" width="1000" height="800"><iframe>

14. meta tag
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="description" content="Your Description">
    <meta name="author" content="Ram">
    <meta name="Keywords" content="HTML">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
